userStories.notes:
File: platform/plugin-sdk/src/fetch.ts, line 39. The current fallback is:

  return new ToolError(message, 'http_error', { category: 'internal' });

This fires for any non-ok status not matched by earlier if-blocks. For 4xx codes, 'internal' is semantically wrong — these are client errors, not server errors. The fix: split the fallback into two branches — one for 4xx (category undefined, retryable false) and one for other unmatched codes (keep current behavior). Add two test cases to platform/plugin-sdk/src/fetch.test.ts using the existing test HTTP server (add /error-409 and /error-413 endpoints). The test server is defined in the beforeAll block starting at line 28.

File: platform/plugin-sdk/src/log.ts, safeSerializeArg function (line 31). Add type checks after the Error check (line 71) and before the JSON fallback (line 76). Use instanceof checks:

  if (value instanceof WeakRef) return '[WeakRef]';
  if (value instanceof WeakMap) return '[WeakMap]';
  if (value instanceof WeakSet) return '[WeakSet]';
  if (value instanceof ArrayBuffer) return '[ArrayBuffer]';
  if (typeof SharedArrayBuffer !== 'undefined' && value instanceof SharedArrayBuffer) return '[SharedArrayBuffer]';

Also update the JSON.stringify replacer (line 78-87) to handle these same types when they appear as nested properties. The replacer already handles functions, bigints, and symbols — add the exotic types in the same pattern.

Tests go in platform/plugin-sdk/src/log.test.ts in the 'safe serialization' describe block (line 137). Follow the existing pattern of collect() + log.info() + assert entries[0]?.data.
